value.0: Reynauld was the reeve of Lockwood Falls hamlet, and had been so since the days of Lord Roderick Llannistaph the senior.
Sir Hamsa was a respected member of the Knights of Agis, and he was the captain of the company at the Tejarn Gate.
These exquisitely crafted boots are made primarily of materials worked by the expert hands of the Dark Elves in the Underdark.
These thin leather gloves are several centuries old, but due to their lasting enchantments, they still provide the wearer with greatly improved physical strength.
Wearing gloves is usually just a matter of fashion, since they do not afford any protection unless infused with magic.
This reddish iron ring allows the wearer to continually withstand both normal and magical flames.
Rings are commonly worn on the fingers as ornamentation, but some are potent magic items.
This simple golden ring is several centuries old, but due to its lasting enchantments, it still provides wearers with a measure of protection from harm as first intended.
Rings are commonly worn on the fingers as ornamentation, but some are potent magic items.
This device appears to be a silver medallion in the shape of a beetle.  It provides the wearer with several highly sought-after benefits, which become known to one who holds the device for one round.
Amulets are necklaces with some form of large decoration of symbol.  Most are ornamental, but some are potent magic items.
This well made longsword is several centuries old, but due the materials utilized in its construction, it still provides a superb advantage to the one bearing it in battle.
This well made tower shield is several centuries old, but thanks to the materials utilized in its construction, it still provides a measure of protection from harm as first intended.
The tower shield is a veritable wall of protection, though it can be quite cumbersome to carry on an adventure.

Dame Glendora was said to have been the only one awake to warn others at the time of the attack on Tejarn Gate. She fought bravely, and her efforts that day were rewarded with her post of captain of the company at North Gate.
This fine cloak has equal measure of fanciness and practicality, common amongst Knights.
Cloaks are simple cloth garments used to protect the wearer from bad wether and other hazards of the open road.
In Tethyr, the longsword was considered a civilized weapon.
Alasdair was the reeve of Watchfield hamlet, meaning that he represented the small number of peasants who live along the Tethir road north of Brost.
The reeve of Fort Briarwood's hamlet, Gregor was known to be an advocate for cooperating with druids in the area.

Quinn was separated from her family during the Interregnum years, so she was fostered at Sentinel Manor by Lady Al-Kamal. As the reeve of the people of the hamlet, she has a lot of responsibility for a person her age.
Brooker was a dependable reeve for Wayside Shrine's hamlet, even if he wore a perpetually worried gaze over it.
Guildmaster Evander oversaw the management of Ieval Boralail's plantation.
Guildmaster Teppin oversaw the operations around the Oakbarrel Brewery, and as a result he was usually quite busy.
Guildmistress Tornelle was quiet but purposefully in her interactions on behalf of the temple of Mystra.
A holy symbol is the physical focus for the manifestation of a god's will.
This finely crafted dagger benefits from a minor enchantment that sharpens its edge.
A basic but versatile weapon, the dagger consists of a double-edged piercing blade that typically ranges from about six to 24 inches in length.
This well made light crossbow is several centuries old, but due to its lasting enchantments, it is still as ready for battle as ever.
Guildmistress Andavi was only a novice in the temple of Ilmater, but she was respected for her shrewd approach to the temples affairs.
The plain, grey robes of the Ilmateri.
The Quartermaster of Brost was responsible for certain specific functions, and answered to the mayor only.
The Quartermaster of Lockwood Falls was responsible for certain specific functions, and answered to the Lord only.
The Quartermaster of Tejarn Gate was responsible for certain specific functions, and answered to the Lord only.
The Quartermaster of Westhaven was responsible for certain specific functions, and answered to the Lord only.
Orcs are an aggressive humanoid species that form into raiding tribes. They are constantly at war with humans, dwarves, elves, goblins, and other orc tribes.
This specialized handaxe is most often found in kitchens or butcher's shops.
The guildmaster of the Lockwood Mines ensured that laborers were paid properly, among other things.
In Tethyr, the longsword was considered a civilized weapon.
The guildmaster of the Lockwood Quarry ensured that laborers were paid properly, among other things.

Galadt was the Guildmaster responsible for ensuring that miners were properly compensated, among other things.

Wearing gloves is usually just a matter of fashion, since they do not afford any protection unless infused with magic.

This girdle was made for the benefit of armored, mounted riders.

In the hands of a properly trained cavalier, it becomes something more.

Those with faith in Red Knight, Siamorphe and Sune might enjoy even further benefits.
This well made longsword was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
The longsword is the weapon most commonly associated with knights and their ilk.  There are many variations in the blade, but all are approximately 35 to 47 inches in length.
As the Guildmaster responsible for labor and production in the Mushroom Farm, Surmein was known for his accountability.
The armor and gambeson of the Blacksriver Militia, led by Sheriff James Blacksriver.
These well worn boots have been broken in and can be moved about in easily while working or fighting.
Boots come in a variety of forms and functions, but they do not add the protection given b y basic armor unless infused with magic.
The cloak worn by the Blacksriver Militia... it was enough to strike fear into some, respect into others.
These helmets boast a protective steel face-plate that is polished to help the wearer see things from their periphery.
Ainsilver was responsible for ensuring that the elves of the Teranthvar Platform could trade their wares with the rest of the county.
Fogveld was the Guildmaster responsible for ensuring that laborers were paid accordingly near the Hunter's Lodges.
Studded leather armor crafted by a skilled Calishite armorsmith.
The Quartermaster of Southspire Hold was responsible for certain specific functions, and answered to the Lord only.

This tent is of some quality make. It seems as though it will help when the temperature drops, remain standing when moderate winds blow, and keep you dry during light rainstorms.
This brazier blazes with warmth. (This object is not persistent and will need to be put back in inventory if you wish to keep it.)
